# Portal Page code style

Use when creating or editing **React + Vite + pp-dev** Portal Page / Custom App code. Mirror for Claude: **`.claude/agents/code-style.md`**.

## Components and files

- **Component filenames** start with a **lowercase** letter — **camelCase**, not PascalCase.
  - ✅ `headerMain.tsx` · ❌ `HeaderMain.tsx`
- **One feature per folder** under `src/components/<feature>/` (kebab-case folder names are fine; keep the **`.tsx` basename camelCase**).
- **Default export** for the main component; name the symbol in **PascalCase** inside the file (`const HeaderMain = () => …`).
- **Search before creating** — extend existing components/hooks/helpers when possible.

## Styles (SCSS modules + BEM)

- **Only `.scss`** — no plain `.css` for component/layout styles.
- **CSS Modules only** — co-locate `<name>.module.scss` next to the component (e.g. `headerMain.module.scss`).
- Import as `styles` and reference classes via the module object:

```tsx
import styles from "./headerMain.module.scss";

<div className={styles.headerMain}>
  <span className={styles.headerMain__title} />
</div>
```

- **BEM in the module** — block `block`, element `block__element`, modifier `block--modifier`:

```scss
.headerMain {
  &__title { … }
  &--compact { … }
}
```

- **Modifiers** in TSX when needed: `clsx(styles.headerMain, { [styles["headerMain--compact"]]: isCompact })`.
- **Shared tokens** — prefer variables/mixins from `src/assets/styles/_variables.scss` and `_mixins.scss`; avoid hardcoded hex when a token exists.
- **Do not** use global class strings for component UI unless matching an existing legacy pattern in the same file.

## App shell (`src/`)

Required layout for app-wide state:

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| **`app-context.ts`** | `createContext`, `AppContextProps`, `useAppContext` |
| **`app-provider.tsx`** | Provider component; holds React state and wraps `<App />` in `main.tsx` |
| **`constants.ts`** | Typed **`PP_VARIABLES`** (from `window`) and **`PP_CONSTANTS`** (in-repo constants) |

### `constants.ts` pattern

```ts
export interface PPVariables {
  WELCOME_MESSAGE: string;
  // …keys injected via index.html window.PP_VARIABLES
}

declare global {
  interface Window {
    PP_VARIABLES: PPVariables;
  }
}

export const PP_VARIABLES: PPVariables =
  typeof window !== "undefined" && typeof window.PP_VARIABLES === "object"
    ? (window.PP_VARIABLES as PPVariables)
    : ({} as PPVariables);

export interface PPConstants {
  ANNOUNCEMENT_CLOSED_STORAGE_KEY: string;
}

export const PP_CONSTANTS: PPConstants = {
  ANNOUNCEMENT_CLOSED_STORAGE_KEY: "PPAnnouncementClosed",
};
```

- **`PP_VARIABLES`** — deployment / MI-injected config (read-only at runtime from `window`).
- **`PP_CONSTANTS`** — static keys and values that belong in source control.
- Extend **`PPVariables`** when adding new `window.PP_VARIABLES` keys; keep types in sync with **`index.html`**.

## `index.html` globals

1. **Favicon** in `<head>`:

```html
<link rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon" sizes="any" href="/img/favicon/favicon.ico">
```

2. **`window.PP_VARIABLES`** — inline script **before `</html>`** (after `</body>` is acceptable if the repo already uses that pattern; prefer immediately before `</html>` in new projects):

```html
<script>
  window.PP_VARIABLES = {
    WELCOME_MESSAGE: "[Welcome message]",
    // …all keys typed in constants.ts
  };
</script>
</html>
```

- Use MI placeholder tokens (`[Welcome message]`, `[Logo]`, etc.) in the template; do not commit instance-specific values.
- **`FAVICON`** may still appear in `PP_VARIABLES` for runtime overrides; the `<link>` above is the static default.

## General habits

- TypeScript for app code; explicit types on public APIs and context shapes.
- Path alias **`@/`** → `src/` for imports outside the current folder.
- Match surrounding file conventions when editing legacy code; apply this rule fully on **new** components and greenfield setup.
